y and historical contexts, Keddie dismantles the biblical basis for Republican positions on hot-button issues like Big Government, taxation, abortion, immigration, and climate change. At the same time, he introduces readers to an ancient Jesus whose life experiences and ethics were totally unlike those of modern Americans, conservatives and liberals alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aBible and politicszUnited States. 0aChristianity and politicszUnited States. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Ideologies / Conservatism & Liberalism.2bisacsh  aBig Government.  aEvangelical Advisory Board.  aFox News pundits.  aNew Testament.  aPresident Trump's administration.  aSmall Government.  aabortion.  abiblical texts.  aclimate change.  aconservative.  acorporatization.  aethics.  afree market capitalism.  agospels.  agun control.  ahealthcare.  ahistorical contexts.  aimmigration.  aoriginal literary.  apolitical agenda.  apoliticians.  apolitics.  asame-sex marriage.  ataxation.  awelfare.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2020z9783110704594oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520976023zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520976023423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520976023.jpg  a978-3-11-069041-5  UC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  